cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.SD 

The paper deals with deep neural networks and their application to multimodal audiovisual activity recognition. The use of Bayesian deep learning methods to provide principled confidence and quantify predictive uncertainty is a key aspect of the work. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with multimodal data, which suggests a possible fit with cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.SD (Sound).
